title.narrative: ACCESS TO NUTRITION-SPECIFIC AND NUTRITION-SENSITIVE INTERVENTIONS

description.narrative: By 2020, the government has an improved capacity to design, implement, monitor and coordinate policies and strategies related to multi-sectoral nutrition (MSN) interventions., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children and women in vulnerable regions demand and use high-quality and proven preventive and curative nutrition interventions, including in emergency situations.

description.narrative: The home fortification with micronutrient powders programme has expanded from 25 health districts (2019) to 41 (2020) exceeding the planned target of 100 per cent of children. In 2021, 17 health districts are implementing the programme. VAS was implemented through routine activities and via sub national mass distribution or coupled with national immunization campaigns. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:01/02/2022
